gomodel:SYNGO_1384  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: tomosyn is a negative regulator of synaptic vesicle priming. in null worms the synaptic response to hypertonic sucrose (which is a measure for the primed vesicle pool) is increased and broader and the reduced response of the known priming factor Munc13 is (partially) compensated. Experimental description: Materials & Methods" ;
